	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually, this operates on the spell's level not the casters.&nbsp;&nbsp;So most casters find the level II focus items work on virtually all their spells until they reach level 49.  At level 49, it's significantly less useful since that is the next spell rank level.  People seem to make this mistake all the time when they post on focus items.<br><br>[note: I say most spells because some classes get a few spells between level 44 and 49.]<br><br>Additionally, I'd like to add that if your only interested in the Focus effect of this item, you may want to look into a Black Iron Medallion   <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=1148" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=1148</a> The BIM can be aquired at a slightly lower level and is quite common on the market.<br><br><br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jan  9 20:46:22 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
